topic.title: Model II Boot Errors Table
topic.shortdesc: List of the possible error messages you may encounter when using the TRS-80 upon boot-up.

stentry.p: Checksum error â€“ possibly a defective ROM.

li.p: Floppy disk expansion unit not on.
Turn on the floppy disk expansion unit.
Insert the diskette again and press .

stentry.p: Controller error. Aborted command: Problem during boot-up of hard disk.
Re-initialize the hard disk or contact RSSC.
CRC error. Invalid data in data field.
Re-initialize the hard disk or contact RSSC.

li.p: Power down, wait 10 seconds, and power up.

stentry.p: If the error occurs again, contact RSSC.
CRC error. Invalid data in ID field.
ID not found. No Boot Track.

li.p: Secondary hard disk drives not turned on.
Turn on your secondary hard disk drives.
Hard disk drive not powered up.

Follow correct procedure: Turn on the hard disk first.
Connect the hard disk drive or operate under floppy disk control.
